1:1 COMMENT "# chained_method_calls.z -- nested calls and source-order evaluation."
1:70 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `consume2 a: (make_val x: 1) b: (make_val x: 2)` exercises the"
3:65 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# recursive hoist: each call-arg expression is itself a call, and"
4:66 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# the typechecker opens a nested call sub-scope while processing"
5:65 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# each one. Args evaluate left-to-right, so the synth temp for"
6:63 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# `a:` is named with a lower counter than the temp for `b:`."
7:61 EOL "\n"
8:1 EOL "\n"
